    <main class="main-panel">
      <div class="page-header-area">
        <h1 class="page-title">Iconography</h1>
        <p class="page-desc">Use icons to accelerate recognition, reinforce hierarchy, and support safe decision-making across endpoint workflows.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="main-content-area">
        <div class="main-content-inner">

          <!-- Intro -->
          <div class="doc-section" style="margin-top: 16px;">
            <p>In Prism, icons are not decoration. They represent device states, OS platforms, severity levels, remote actions, navigation structures, automation states, and system feedback.</p>
            <p>A strong iconography system helps admins scan faster, reduce cognitive load, and act confidently in high-density enterprise environments.</p>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider">

          <!-- Iconography principles -->
          <div class="doc-section" id="principles">
            <h2>Iconography principles</h2>
            <p>Prism iconography follows the same system logic as the reference: universal meaning, simplicity, harmony, and intentional use.</p>

            <!-- Principle 1 -->
            <h3 id="universal-understanding">1. Design for universal understanding</h3>
            <p>Use familiar metaphors that are immediately recognizable.</p>

